msgid "location.embark.name"
msgstr "Embarking"
msgid "location.embark.description"
msgstr "Embark ships at nearby docks."
msgid "location.embark.longdesc"
msgstr "Use the nearby docks to embark on ships and continue your travel by sea."
msgid "location.embark.description2"
msgstr "Return to your ships."
msgid "location.embark.longdesc2"
msgstr "Return to your nearby ships and continue your travel by sea."
msgid "location.embark.done"
msgstr "You have embarked upon ships at %dockname% and are now travelling at sea.<br /> The ships can land you at most coastal locations, but you can only embark at a dock with the appropriate permissions or, of course, return to where you landed as your ships will wait for up to 30 days for you there. This means if you are not careful, landing can be a one-way trip.<br /> To land, simply travel towards land. You will disembark at the first point where your travel hits solid ground.
"
msgid "location.embark.done2"
msgstr "You have returned to your ships and are now travelling at sea.<br /> The ships can land you at most coastal locations, but you can only embark at a dock with the appropriate permissions or, of course, return to where you landed as your ships will wait for up to 30 days for you there. This means if you are not careful, landing can be a one-way trip.<br /> To land, simply travel towards land. You will disembark at the first point where your travel hits solid ground."
msgid "location.giveship.name"
msgstr "Give ship"
msgid "location.giveship.description"
msgstr "Give your ship to someone else."
msgid "location.giveship.longdesc"
msgstr "Grant control of your ship to someone else, allowing that person to use it, but losing the ship for yourself."
msgid "location.giveship.intro"
msgstr "You can give your ship to someone else, so that noble can use it, instead of you. Because once you have given your ship away, you can not use it yourself anymore.<br /> Giving a ship away does not extend the time the captain will wait, it is still 30 days after you landed.
"
msgid "location.giveship.success"
msgstr "You have given control of your ship to %newowner% now."
msgid "location.givegold.name"
msgstr "Give gold"
msgid "location.givegold.description"
msgstr "Give some of your gold to someone else."
msgid "location.givegold.intro"
msgstr "You can give some (or all) of your gold to someone else. Simply choose the amount and the recipient, and a servant will run with a sack of gold.<br /> You currently have %gold% gold.
"
msgid "location.givegold.success"
msgstr "You have given %amount% gold to %target%."
msgid "location.inn.name"
msgstr "Visit Inn"
msgid "location.inn.intro"
msgstr "In the inn, you can hear rumours from abroad, especially about what other lords offer for prospective knights. And if you are looking for sell-swords, soldiers of fortune, men-at-arms - in a word: Mercenaries, the inn is where you will most likely find them.<br /> They are usually easy to spot as they are looking for employers the same way you are looking for them. Their services,  however, are less easy. They will follow you as long as you pay them well. You can also not retrain, assign or set them as militia. And you can only disband them all at once.
"
msgid "location.inn.description"
msgstr "Get a drink and check for rumours and mercenaries."
msgid "location.library.name"
msgstr "Library"
msgid "location.library.intro"
msgstr "At the library of %settlement%, scrolls and maps are available for your perusal. The local scholars and cartographers have collected data not readily available unless curated.<br /> <i>(for maximum usefulness, when you click on the maps you get a full-size image. Use your browsers \"back\" button to return to this page.)</i>
"
msgid "location.library.maps.name"
msgstr "Maps"
msgid "location.library.maps.allrealms"
msgstr "all realms of the world"
msgid "location.library.maps.2ndrealms"
msgstr "second-level realms"
msgid "location.library.maps.majorrealms"
msgstr "sovereign realms of the world"
msgid "location.library.top.name"
msgstr "World Rumours"
msgid "location.library.top.realms"
msgstr "The scholars have gathered rumours and travel reports and are listing the largest realms of the known world as follows:"
msgid "location.library.top.settlements"
msgstr "From travellers, scholars and other sources, they have also compiled a list of the largest settlements:"
msgid "location.library.description"
msgstr "Visit the scholars and cartographers at the local library."
msgid "location.temple.name"
msgstr "Visit Temple"
msgid "location.temple.intro"
msgstr "The local temple of %settlement% keeps a record of births and deaths, allowing you to trace back the settlements development into time.<br /> The priests have prepared a nice graph for you. As they explain, the height of the line shows the population, and the far right is yesterday, while the line further to the left goes into the past, with the number at the bottom showing how many days into the past.
"
msgid "location.temple.description"
msgstr "Visit the local temple and its priests."
msgid "location.barracks.name"
msgstr "Inspect Barracks"
msgid "location.barracks.intro"
msgstr "Thanks to local barracks of %settlement% providing housing for its soldiers, it can also keep a record of militia within the settlement.<br /> A clerk has prepared a nice graph for you. As he explains, the height of the line shows the number of militia in the settlement on any given day, with higher meaning more. The far right shows yesterday, while the line further to the left goes into the past, with the number at the bottom showing how many days into the past.
"
msgid "location.barracks.description"
msgstr "Inspect the local barracks and soldier records."
msgid "location.dungeons.name"
msgstr "Enter Dungeon"
msgid "location.dungeons.description"
msgstr "Explore the nearby dungeon."
msgid "nearby.spy.name"
msgstr "Spy on an estate"
msgid "nearby.spy.description"
msgstr "Send a spy to the nearest settlement."
msgid "nearby.spy.intro"
msgstr "You can leave one of your spies behind in this settlement, and he will keep you updated about everything that is going on, supplying you with access to the settlements event log and local details, just as if you were there yourself.<br /> Over time, the spy might be discovered, or disappear.
"
msgid "nearby.spy.intro2"
msgstr "You can send one of your spies to infiltrate this settlement. There is a reasonable chance that he will make it inside, but he could also be captured during the attempt. If he makes it, he will keep you updated about everything that is going on, supplying you with access to the settlements event log and local details, just as if you were there yourself.<br /> Over time, the spy might be discovered, or disappear.
"
msgid "control.name"
msgstr "local control actions"
msgid "control.all"
msgstr "all control actions"
msgid "control.take.name"
msgstr "take control"
msgid "control.take.description"
msgstr "Declare your lordship over these people and make this settlement yours."
msgid "control.take.intro"
msgstr "In order to command the resources and population of this %type%, you need to take control of it first.<br /> This process simply takes time. In a small settlement, you simply convince the people directly, while in larger settlements you will take control of the local administration.<br /> The amount of time required depends on the settlement size and on forces supporting and/or opposing you. This includes the local militia, which will automatically oppose you.<br /> Taking control of this settlement will take an estimated %time%, if nobody else interferes.
"
msgid "control.take.newbie"
msgstr "Are you absolutely sure you know what you are doing? This is a <i>hostile action</i> on a settlement owned by another player. Your character is new in the game and could easily <i>be killed</i> in retaliation.<br /> Unless you are certain and know what you are doing, talking to the settlement owner via the <a href=\"%url%\">messages tab</a> is very likely a much better idea.
"
msgid "control.take.long"
msgstr "You noticed that it will take a very long time to take control here? If you know what you are doing, go ahead,  we won't stop you, but probably you should bring more troops, reduce the militia by attacking first or gain the support of allies who will aid you.
"
msgid "control.take.owned"
msgstr "This settlement is currently controlled by %owner%."
msgid "control.take.others.title"
msgstr "Other Control attempts"
msgid "control.take.others.intro"
msgstr "The following nobles are also currently trying to take control of this settlement. Without diplomacy or battle, this will likely result in a mess of conflicting claims resolving over time. If you want to take control yourself, you will almost certainly have to make them all stop, either by convincing them or by attacking them.<br /> Your other alternative is supporting someone else, which will speed up their process of taking the settlement."
msgid "control.take.defended"
msgstr "Defending forces are making it more difficult to raise your banner. Attacking and culling them first might speed up your action.
"
msgid "control.take.undefended"
msgstr "There are no defending forces at this settlement, making it very easy and quick to take control.
"
msgid "control.take.realm"
msgstr "in the name of"
msgid "control.take.submit"
msgstr "take control"
msgid "control.take.success"
msgstr "You are now in the process of taking control of this settlement. The process will take an estimated %time%, though this estimate will change with the support or opposition of other nobles."
msgid "control.takeX.name"
msgstr "defend against taking"
msgid "control.takeX.description"
msgstr "Your estate is currently being claimed by others, oppose them."
msgid "control.changerealm.name"
msgstr "Change realm allegiance."
msgid "control.changerealm.description"
msgstr "Decide to which of your realms this settlement is aligned."
msgid "control.changerealm.intro"
msgstr "As the owner of %settlement%, you decide which realm it is considered to belong to. While this is a simple matter of declaration to change, the political consequences can be massive, so consider them well.<br /> Also remember that your membership in realms depends on you holding estates within their hierarchy, so changing the allegiance of a settlement can result in you leaving a realm if it is your only estate within.
"
msgid "control.changerealm.current"
msgstr "%settlement% is currently a part of %realm%."
msgid "control.changerealm.nocurrent"
msgstr "%settlement% is not considered part of any realm at this time."
msgid "control.changerealm.realm"
msgstr "change to realm"
msgid "control.changerealm.submit"
msgstr "change allegiance"
msgid "control.changerealm.success"
msgstr "You have successfully changed the allegiance of this settlement to %newrealm%."
msgid "control.changerealm.leftrealm"
msgstr "Since you now hold no estates within %oldrealm% anymore, you are no longer a member of that realm."
msgid "control.changerealm.fail.same"
msgstr "The settlement already belongs to this realm."
msgid "control.grant.name"
msgstr "grant control"
msgid "control.grant.description"
msgstr "Hand over control over these people to another noble."
msgid "control.grant.intro"
msgstr "Settlements you control can be handed off to someone else.<br /> Note that this does <em>not</em> make the recipient your vassal automatically. This action merely hands over control, questions of vassalage and legitimacy are for you to resolve.
"
msgid "control.grant.introwr"
msgstr "You can grant a settlement \"with its realm\", meaning you make the new lord a member of the realm the settlement belongs to. Alternatively, you can grant without, which makes the settlement independent before granting it and is useful to giving settlements away to other realms.
"
msgid "control.grant.to"
msgstr "grant control to"
msgid "control.grant.withrealm"
msgstr "with realm?"
msgid "control.grant.withrealm2"
msgstr "If you grant an estate \"with realm\", the estate will stay in its current realm and the new lord will join that realm if he is not already a member."
msgid "control.grant.keepclaim"
msgstr "keep claim?"
msgid "control.grant.keepclaim2"
msgstr "If you keep a claim to the estate, you grant it \"in fief\", but you continue to consider it your property. The claim will allow you to take it back easily."
msgid "control.grant.success"
msgstr "You have now given control over this settlement to %newowner%."
msgid "control.grant.queued"
msgstr "You will soon be meeting with %newowner% and arrange the details of the transfer, as well as informing the settlement leaders."
msgid "control.rename.name"
msgstr "rename settlement"
msgid "control.rename.description"
msgstr "Change the name of this settlement."
msgid "control.rename.intro"
msgstr "As the lord of this %type%, you can change its name to make it easier to distinguish, or to placate your ego."
msgid "control.rename.newname"
msgstr "new name"
msgid "control.rename.submit"
msgstr "change name"
msgid "control.rename.tooshort"
msgstr "Settlement names should be at least 3 characters long."
msgid "control.rename.success"
msgstr "You have now declared that this place shall be known as \"%newname%\".<br /> Maps and signs will be updated at once.
"
msgid "control.rename.queued"
msgstr "The settlement leaders have been instructed to change the name of this place to \"%newname%\".<br /> Maps and signs will be updated over the next few hours. You will see the change completed soon."
msgid "control.culture.name"
msgstr "change culture"
msgid "control.culture.description"
msgstr "Change the culture of this settlement."
msgid "control.culture.intro"
msgstr "As the lord of this <em>%current%</em> %type%, you can change its culture.<br /> The culture of a settlement defines its flair, visuals and the names of the entourage and soldiers recruited here.<br /> This should be used sparingly, as it would be unrealistic to change all the time. It also makes a lot more sense to communicate with your neighors and set up cultural areas.<br /> <br /> The central european is available to everyone. Additional cultures can be bought on your account page (Credits and Gifts). If you conquer a settlement belonging to a culture you do not own, it will retain its culture, but you can only change settlements to cultures you own.
"
msgid "control.culture.newculture"
msgstr "new culture"
msgid "control.culture.success"
msgstr "You have now declared that this place follows the %culture% culture.
"
msgid "control.culture.queued"
msgstr "The settlement leaders have been instructed to adapt to a %culture% culture.<br /> You will see the change completed soon."
msgid "control.permissions.name"
msgstr "manage permissions"
msgid "control.permissions.description"
msgstr "Set and change permissions for others"
msgid "control.permissions.intro"
msgstr "As lord of %settlement%, you can determine how the settlement officials should treat others, if they should allow them into the settlement at all, if they can use the resources of the settlement to resupply or even pick up recruits.<br /> To make everything more accessible, this system uses the <a href=\"%listsurl%\">lists system</a> to define permission owners.
"
msgid "control.permissions.general"
msgstr "general permissions"
msgid "control.permissions.specific"
msgstr "specific permissions"
msgid "control.permissions.spawn"
msgstr "allow new characters to spawn here?"
msgid "control.permissions.thralls"
msgstr "allow slavery (thralls) ?"
msgid "control.permissions.submit"
msgstr "set new permissions"
msgid "control.permissions.success"
msgstr "Your new permissions have been saved."
msgid "control.quests.name"
msgstr "manage quests"
msgid "control.quests.description"
msgstr "Create and edit quests for this settlement"
msgid "control.quests.intro"
msgstr "As lord of %settlement%, you can set quests for other characters passing by to complete.<br /> A quest can be absolutely any task that you can describe in words and where you can determine if it was completed or not. It will be written on message boards everywhere inside the region, so it is available to anyone who enters the region, even if they do not or are not allowed to enter the settlement itself.<br /> Quests should also contain a reward. This as well can be anything. Quests can be completed once or many times, as you wish. In essence, quests are entirely free-form and you determine everything, including if you will give out the promised reward or betray the knight you finished your quest.<br /> Quests are public knowledge, so other people can see all past and current quests, who has taken them up, if they think the quest was completed, if you agree and if they consider the reward to be received or not.
"
msgid "control.quests.new"
msgstr "Create New Quest"
msgid "control.quests.create"
msgstr "To create a quest, describe the task to do and the reward given.<br /> You can give a short summary, a long description and a description of the reward. You should include all important information, including whether the quest reward will be given only to the first to complete it, or to multiple people, and on which conditions, such as evidence of conclusion, or time limits.
"
msgid "military.name"
msgstr "military actions"
msgid "military.all"
msgstr "all military actions"
msgid "military.other"
msgstr "other military actions"
msgid "military.disengage.name"
msgstr "Disengage"
msgid "military.disengage.description"
msgstr "try to avoid the upcoming battle."
msgid "military.disengage.longdesc"
msgstr "attempt to disengage from the forces attacking you and avoid the battle that is currently being forced upon you."
msgid "military.disengage.intro"
msgstr "You are being attacked, and you may or may not be looking forward to this battle. As the enemy is still maneuvering to engage you, you can also still escape. With your current unit size, it will take %time% to pack up everything and leave, at which point you will find out if you succeed in making a run for it, or are already surrounded.
"
msgid "military.disengage.battles"
msgstr "choose the battle(s) you want to disengage from"
msgid "military.disengage.submit"
msgstr "avoid battle"
msgid "military.disengage.success"
msgstr "You have instructed your troops to pack up and avoid the upcoming battle. You might want to also travel away or you will probably be engaged again."
msgid "military.evade.name"
msgstr "Evade"
msgid "military.evade.description"
msgstr "evade enemy forces."
msgid "military.evade.longdesc"
msgstr "Instruct your troops to automatically attempt to disengage from any battles you are forced into."
msgid "military.evade.intro"
msgstr "You can instruct your troops to avoid any battles you are forced into. While this might sound like something you want to do all the time, also keep in mind that if you are travelling with a larger army of realm mates, it might mean some of you evade the battle and others don't, splitting forces up.<br /> This action will remain in effect until you cancel it and apply to any and all battles that you do not voluntarily join.<br /> <br /> Since enemy troops could enage you again after a successful evade, it is strongly recommended that you also set travel away from your enemy in order to avoid being re-engaged.
"
msgid "military.evade.submit"
msgstr "evade all battles"
msgid "military.evade.success"
msgstr "Your troops are now instructed to immediately disengage if a battle is forced upon you."
msgid "military.settlement.all"
msgstr "all military actions on settlements"
msgid "military.settlement.defend.name"
msgstr "defend settlement"
msgid "military.settlement.defend.description"
msgstr "set your troops up to defend this settlement, should it get attacked."
msgid "military.settlement.defend.intro"
msgstr "Order your soldiers to defend %settlement%.<br /> They will set up defenses, making use of any fortifications available, and defend the settlement against anyone ordering an attack.
"
msgid "military.settlement.defend.submit"
msgstr "set up defenses"
msgid "military.settlement.defend.queued"
msgstr "Your soldiers are now preparing for an attack, and are ready to defend.
"
msgid "military.settlement.attack.name"
msgstr "attack settlement"
msgid "military.settlement.attack.description"
msgstr "invade this settlement in order to kill or drive away its defenders."
msgid "military.settlement.attack.intro"
msgstr "Order your soldiers to attack %settlement%.<br /> There will be a battle between your forces as well as any other attackers, against the settlement militia and anyone choosing to defend. If you are victorious, you have forced your way into the settlement, and actions such as taking control of the settlement for yourself or attacking nobles inside will appear.<br /> <i>Once initiated, battles cannot be cancelled. Once you are committed, you are committed. Decide wisely.</i>
"
msgid "military.settlement.attack.submit"
msgstr "attack!"
msgid "military.settlement.attack.success"
msgstr "Your soldiers are preparing for the attack and will commence battle shortly."
msgid "military.settlement.attack.reminder"
msgstr "Remember that in order to not just attack, but also take control of the settlement, you need to issue a <a href=\"%url%\">%take%</a> action as well."
msgid "military.settlement.loot.name"
msgstr "loot settlement"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.description"
msgstr "plunder this settlement for valuables and resources."
msgid "military.settlement.loot.intro"
msgstr "Looting enemy settlements allows you to take resources or thralls by force and transfer them to any estate of your choice (preferably yours, typically).<br /< You can also loot for personal profit or raid the workshops for supply, or simply burn the place down.<br /> The more options you select, the longer everything will take and the more distributed the effects will be. To maximize the efficiency of specific goals, you should focus on one or two options.<br /> Like battles, looting commits you - once you have initiated a looting action, you cannot cancel it or travel elsewhere, until it is complete.
"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.owner"
msgstr "As you are the lord of this settlement, you can <i>steal wealth</i> very effectively with no negative effects. You will call this an unscheduled tax collection."
msgid "military.settlement.loot.outside"
msgstr "As you are outside the settlement, you can only loot the countryside, which offers fewer targets. Fight, bribe or trick your way inside the settlement for more effective looting."
msgid "military.settlement.loot.time"
msgstr "The selected looting options will take <span id=\"time\">4</span> hours to complete."
msgid "military.settlement.loot.target"
msgstr "send plunder to"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.options"
msgstr "loot actions"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.option.thralls"
msgstr "take thralls"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.option.resources"
msgstr "take resources"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.option.supply"
msgstr "steal supply"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.option.wealth"
msgstr "steal wealth"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.option.burn"
msgstr "burn down buildings"
msgid "military.settlement.loot.submit"
msgstr "begin looting"
msgid "military.battles.initiate.name"
msgstr "initiate battle"
msgid "military.battles.initiate.description"
msgstr "prepare for battle with other nobles."
msgid "military.battles.initiate.intro"
msgstr "Face your enemies in battle by positioning your troops so they cannot easily retreat, forcing them into an encounter.<br /> By declaring one or more primary targets, you decide who to engage. However, everyone within reach of the battle can join in on either your or their side, so you cannot be sure who you will face in the end.<br /> Battle preparations take time depending on the size of the involved forces, so both you and your target(s) have a short time to call in allies for support.<br /> If you are inside a settlement, you can only attack others who are also inside (but you can leave to attack those outside). If you are outside a settlement, you cannot attack nobles inside a settlement, you will have to attack the settlement to get inside.<br /> <i>Once initiated, battles cannot be cancelled. Once you are committed, you are committed. Decide wisely.</i>
"
msgid "military.battles.initiate.success"
msgstr "You are now engaging the enemy and battle prepartions are being made on both sides, estimated time until the battle will commence is %time%, but could change as you and/or the enemy get more support.<br /> Your enemy has been notified of the impending attack."
msgid "military.battles.join.name"
msgstr "join battle"
msgid "military.battles.join.description"
msgstr "join a nearby battle and choose your side."
msgid "military.battles.join.intro"
msgstr "One or more battles have been initiated nearby. Choose which side to fight on."
